results.title: Top spin and back spin strokes
results.creator_credit: Don Kelly, Richard Hackett and Gerard Holdsworth Productions
results.brief_description:
Episode number 2 of Series “Table tennis”
Part 2 of a series of four films which show that table tennis is a very competitive sport played throughout the world by people of all ages. The game is built around attacking and defensive strokes. Some of these strokes are demonstrated like: topspin; forehand drive; backhand drive; backspin, forehand chop and backhand chop.

results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Table tennis. - Part 4.”.
Part 4 of a series of four films which show that table tennis is a very competitive sport played throughout the world by people of all ages. This film shows specialised strokes and also stresses the importance of the service as a match winning technique. Other matters dealt with are: Balloon Defence, Technique, Hitting the Balloon Defence (Jump Kill), the Drop Shot, Side-spin and services

results.title: Men, machines and the secretary
results.creator_credit: Bill Young, Ian Rosenbloom and British Broadcasting Corporation
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Systems Organisation the Management of Complexity”.
Examines the London headquarters of Texaco, a multi-national oil company, to case study the introduction of word processors which demanded a major reorganisation of the company’s use of secretaries.

results.title: The Company computers and the unions
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Systems Organisation the Management of Complexity”.
This film was made at the Pearl Assurance Company where recent developments in office technology, specifically microcomputers, is beginning to have a dramatic impact on the kinds of work that the staff at Pearl produce.
